pr_title: Default tag:dev-latest; parameterise Percona/Perconalab Dockerhub org
pr_body:
1.  Default tag set to `dev-latest` when `--dev` option is provided. 
2.  Parameterised percona/perconalab Dockerhub organization name using `docker_org `variable.

1. Improve options passing functionality in script using `getopt`
      - command line options no longer hard-coded
2. Refactor `mysql/mongodb/postgresql` configuration into separate functions
3. Added `pmm2-client` installation using `yum/apt`
     - installs latest ` public release` of pmm2-client using `percona-release` repository by default

@puneet0191

pr_body:
1. `--dev` flag now installs pmm2-client from `original testing` repository of `percona-release`
    (default pmm2-client installation being the public release)
2. Fixed minor indentation issues 
3. Pull in changes form percona/pmm-qa/master branch

pr_title: Update with master, installation refactor, ssl flag fix
pr_body:
Changelog:
- [x] Added `--ssl` flag to make PMM setup end to end automated

- [x] Updated `GSOC-2020` branch with percona master branch _(merge conflicts - solved)_

- [x] Refactored pmm installation and setup (Before this, option to install only the client or only the server wasn't available. `--setup` configured both client+server together on same machine)
  - added `--setup-client`
  - added `--setup-server`

pr_title: AddClient error hotfix, Fixed get_download_link.sh file permissions
pr_body:
- [x] fixed get_download_link.sh permission error (downloading this script was fixed previously)
- [x] Here sanity check prevented --addclient option on machine having only PMM-Client to execute. So addclient didn't work on such machines. Fixed by removing the sanity check.

- [x] Pulled new changes from `percona/pmm-qa/master` branch to GSOC-2020 branch
- [x] Fixed merge conflicts
